                                        <LineBreak />
                                        <LineBreak />
                                        <Run Text="When performing air-to-air combat within visual range of the target aircraft, even the modern monitors are unable to provide the necessary resolution to accurately represent enemy aircraft at realistic ranges. The fine details of an aircraft seen flying in the real world typically are not visible in the simulator at the same simulated distances. Pilots use these details to help determine things like the pitch, bank and heading of the target aircraft."/>
